originalText.text: Great hostel, great host! Was greeted with a warm hand towel and 5 different choices of shampoo. Continental breakfast was served but the yogurt was full fat and not non fat like I requested.

originalText.text: Before stepping foot into the unit, I was greeted by the host in the lobby and immediately searched for the nearest map as I was lost in his eyes. As my knees lost their integrity, the host firmly gripped my hand and sent an inebriating spark up my spine. He guided me up to his palace, where I was welcomed with a flutter of doves and a fleet  of waitresses carrying platters of hors d’oeuvres. Despite the jazz band playing seductive blues in the corner and the bottles of champagne popping like fireworks, I couldn’t take my eyes off the host. He was mysterious yet charming, short yet full of presence, and had a smile that gave Times Square a run for its light bill money. I can’t thank the host enough for this experience. I cannot wait to return.
